scenes.label: *start
texts: Hey. Sorry about the late visit.
You're right on time, actually. I just learned something about that woman you almost ran over.
I've heard it before. A hacker, right?
She's the first in the quest rankings, I'm sure you're aware she's considered "wizard-level" by her peers.
...She's certainly someone who could do that CANBUS hack.
You mentioned that the meeting with those two didn't go well?
Yeah. It was an interestin' chat, but... I'm not sure about either of them.
I couldn't tell if they're tellin' the truth or just pullin' some smoke and mirror shit.
I looked into what you said they said, and they might've been more honest than you think.
You found somethin' about the airport thing?
I did. The Vatican really did send some special plane to Haneda, secretly.
No. It returned to Rome this morning.
The plane was also visited yesterday afternoon by the Chief Cabinet Secretary, as well as the Ministers of Defense and Foreign Affairs.
And all three of them cleared their schedules to be there.
That's one luxury audience. Makes it sound like a real big deal.
Does that mean that the Vatican requested something from our government?
I'll pass this on to the boy and the girl. That all right with ya?
As long as they don't make it public.
I looked into her, as well. I still don't have anything confirming her real name...
...But she arrived in Japan three days ago. One day before the army caught up with her.
She was spotted by a camera in the Ooi-futo <tips,35,BPTS> base.
Some freight from Rome arrived 20 minutes before the sighting. Eyewitnesses report seeing her at the BPTS base on the other side too.
This supports claims of the Vatican's involvement.
...She smuggled herself into Japan among high-orbit freight? That kinda shit is tempting death...
Was she that desperate to make it to Japan?
